Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.65,0:01:47.11,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)\pos(314,366)}Izu, Shizuoka Prefecture
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.19,0:01:50.11,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,0)\pos(314,366)}Genkai Temple Gate
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.01,0:01:56.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is so beautiful! This is a great change.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.84,0:02:01.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and it's all thanks to you for winning this prize in the contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.31,0:02:05.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're the one who solved the puzzle, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.48,0:02:08.46,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}It was unbelievably easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.43,0:02:12.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.97,0:02:16.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.00,0:02:19.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate it here—this place is just depressing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.34,0:02:23.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These free trips are really lousy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.01,0:02:24.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.56,0:02:27.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who got all excited when you first heard about this free trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.83,0:02:30.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.52,0:02:34.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just go to back to the hotel and soak in the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.07,0:02:37.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but smoking isn't allowed on temple grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.58,0:02:37.75,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)\pos(314,350)}Shigekichi Okabe (55)\NTemple Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.75,0:02:39.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.57,0:02:42.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.33,0:02:43.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.72,0:02:48.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, it's true this place might be somewhat boring for tourists.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.62,0:02:55.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true! You don't see sights like this in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.03,0:02:57.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It cleanses my soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.09,0:03:00.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How nice of you. You're young, but admirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.77,0:03:04.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want, I can give you a tour of the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.36,0:03:05.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Could you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.92,0:03:07.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.72,0:03:09.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be rude, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.83,0:03:11.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.39,0:03:15.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This temple was built 400 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.73,0:03:18.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,400 years ago? It's very old.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.82,0:03:23.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to its age, there are many historical sites here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.18,0:03:31.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For example, an old well near the pagoda was used well until the middle of the Edo period.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.25,0:03:33.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What made them stop using it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.92,0:03:36.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It suddenly went dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.88,0:03:41.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Legend says that a young heartbroken woman cried for three days in front of the well,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.68,0:03:46.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and when her tears dried, the water in the well filled her eyes and dried.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.17,0:03:49.68,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Man, talk about nonsense...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.99,0:04:06.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a frightening legend behind this pagoda.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.93,0:04:09.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What legend?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.33,0:04:13.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In the beginning of the Edo period,\Nthere was a young monk
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.77,0:04:18.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who the head priest picked as his successor for this temple, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.14,0:04:24.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fsp-0.3\fs34}He fell in love with a girl from the village, broke his vows, left the temple, and ran away to marry her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.15,0:04:30.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But supposedly due to a curse, the monk was taken away by a goshawk
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.81,0:04:34.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and was found dead later on, hanging from the pagoda.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.77,0:04:36.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How horrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.23,0:04:39.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's more. Midway through the Edo period,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.33,0:04:46.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,a ruthless priest sold the temple's furniture to have money and used the money for liquor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.32,0:04:49.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, he disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.16,0:04:55.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A few days later, he was found dead,\Nhanging from the pagoda.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.33,0:05:09.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Since then, it's been said that anyone who breaks the temple's vows will be cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.64,0:05:12.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't make that scary face.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.77,0:05:17.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.73,0:05:18.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tankai-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.59,0:05:22.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be scared. He's the head priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.70,0:05:24.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The head priest?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.82,0:05:29.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're bringing a family here now? What are you looking for this time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.16,0:05:29.00,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,0)\pos(314,350)}Tankai (64)\NGenkai Temple Head Priest
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.04,0:05:33.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, wait. They're just tourists.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.23,0:05:36.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They look suspicious. I don't trust them!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.99,0:05:40.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bring strangers here without my permission!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.13,0:05:42.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the tourists are what make the temple...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.06,0:05:44.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.38,0:05:47.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that people will desecrate the temple for that very reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.61,0:05:49.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.28,0:05:55.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But soon, punishment shall befall the unbeliever...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.12,0:05:59.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The punishment of the temple's curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.36,0:06:09.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.32,0:06:14.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, a tour company took over this property
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.58,0:06:18.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and they want to build a theme park.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.76,0:06:19.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\clip(0,0,640,480)\move(-8,259,201,259)\bord0\shad0\c&H282347&\fs22}KEEP OUT
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.01,0:06:22.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the area's going to change?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.50,0:06:24.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.30,0:06:27.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The head priest is opposing it, saying he was tricked.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.52,0:06:29.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's bitter even towards tourists now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.53,0:06:33.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he has some nerve, scaring people like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.43,0:06:35.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.54,0:06:36.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.40,0:06:41.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, my dad's a bit short-tempered...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.85,0:06:45.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't apologise, it's all my fault...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.24,0:06:50.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, your father wouldn't happen to be Kogoro Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.33,0:06:54.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he's a detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:58.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! As I figured, he's that famous great detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.45,0:07:02.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I have a nice story to tell my grandson!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.17,0:07:13.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor. Thank you for inviting us to dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.14,0:07:16.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The honor is ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.60,0:07:19.15,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,450)\pos(314,330)}Yosuke Kajimura (43)\NOda Tours Director\NHotel Oda Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.03,0:07:22.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our hotel just opened, so having a famous person such as yourself staying here is great publicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.27,0:07:28.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm at your service if I'm needed!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.26,0:07:31.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You certainly have a beautiful hotel here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.79,0:07:33.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.29,0:07:38.55,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,800)\pos(314,350)}Hideaki Oda (56)\NPresident of Oda Tours
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.99,0:07:38.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The theme park that I proposed building will be finished next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.64,0:07:41.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This place will become even more enjoyable!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.46,0:07:45.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? It must be costing you a lot of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.30,0:07:48.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, well, about 8 billion yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.93,0:07:53.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But once it's finished,  I'm expecting to make over 10 billion yen annually.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.18,0:07:55.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.48,0:07:58.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I apologise for my rudeness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.14,0:08:00.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the hotel's general manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.81,0:08:02.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be impertinent, Kajimura!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.20,0:08:08.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were careless. How did you {\i1}not{\i0} realize that the great detective Kogoro Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.97,0:08:13.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was staying here until Okabe told you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.31,0:08:15.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you learn from this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.13,0:08:17.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.41,0:08:20.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't you going to Tokyo tonight on a business trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.23,0:08:21.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Should you really be wasting time here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.97,0:08:22.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.88,0:08:26.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, Mouri-{\i1}sama{\i0}, please enjoy your stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.93,0:08:30.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's totally useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.22,0:08:35.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry. I sometimes forget myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.73,0:08:38.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were pretty harsh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.36,0:08:42.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I always get like that when it comes to business.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.38,0:08:46.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a diamond on your tie pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.30,0:08:52.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's no big deal.\NIt's only about five carats.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.85,0:08:57.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Five carats? It's huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.08,0:09:00.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Dad! You're embarassing me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.02,0:09:04.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, young lady.\NYour father's just acting naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.48,0:09:07.96,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}That's {\i1}natural{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.96,0:09:10.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, your cigar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.56,0:09:13.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Where's the receipt?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.13,0:09:16.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.83,0:09:19.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez. I can write it off as company expenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.60,0:09:24.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you always carry so much money with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.73,0:09:27.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This? This is just petty change.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.83,0:09:29.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate credit cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.63,0:09:37.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at yourself, enjoying a meal...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.29,0:09:39.21,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)\pos(314,350)}Shunkai (26)\NTankai's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.96,0:09:39.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a disgrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.90,0:09:43.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If it isn't the heir to the Genkai Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.15,0:09:46.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you finish your training at the head temple yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.17,0:09:48.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My father's ignorant about financial affairs, so you managed to deceive him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.95,0:09:51.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you won't get away with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.09,0:09:53.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I came back to the temple to make sure of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.93,0:09:57.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, watch what you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.18,0:09:59.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You and my father have carefully discussed the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.61,0:10:00.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.93,0:10:03.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You told my father he should sign over the temple's deed to Oda Tours temporarily
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.57,0:10:06.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to raise funds for the preservation of the temple's environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.81,0:10:09.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He trusted your advice!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.41,0:10:14.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But now he's ready to take you to court!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.07,0:10:17.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all you have to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.91,0:10:18.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.82,0:10:22.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm entertaining my guests right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.78,0:10:25.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to tell me anything else, come to my office tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.34,0:10:30.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you think this is the last you'll hear of me, you're sadly mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.63,0:10:32.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.65,0:10:40.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the interruptions. This place is like a mad house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.43,0:10:43.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're having problems with the people at the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.39,0:10:45.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.72,0:10:48.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're suspicious of the development plans,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.73,0:10:54.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and some of them are protesting, saying we'll destroy the temple's atmosphere and whatnot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.83,0:10:57.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to gain from the tourism business too,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.12,0:10:59.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but they're a bunch of idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.45,0:11:05.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}, didn't they say a curse would fall on those who harm the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.01,0:11:08.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't the time for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.45,0:11:13.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I already know about that legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.29,0:11:16.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Many people warned me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.11,0:11:20.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that can be used to draw in tourists, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.89,0:11:23.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a matter of how one looks at things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.81,0:11:28.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}This guy's a shark...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.52,0:11:48.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Mouri Detective Agency...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.22,0:11:50.98,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}It's me, Okabe! I'm the one who showed you around the temple yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.98,0:11:53.27,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}It's terrible! The curse, it came true!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.25,0:11:56.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? The curse?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.54,0:11:59.02,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Please come to the temple, right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.92,0:12:02.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.93,0:12:09.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-{\i1}sensei{\i0}! This way, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.64,0:12:13.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on! I want an explanation!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.73,0:12:16.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The terrifying curse came true!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.91,0:12:27.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What curse? He's just reciting the morning prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.96,0:12:27.88,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(450,0)\pos(314,360)}Chōka (Morning Prayers)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.68,0:12:31.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that. Look over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.17,0:12:41.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oda-{\i1}san{\i0} was...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.59,0:12:44.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.81,0:12:58.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The crime lab's done with their investigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.81,0:13:03.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so the corpse is going to be lowered now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.71,0:13:06.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How does it look?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.49,0:13:08.49,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)\pos(444,336)}Detective Yokomizo\NShizuoka Prefectural Police
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.06,0:13:10.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was found with the rope tied to the railing on one end,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.94,0:13:14.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the other end was swung around the edge of the roof and around his neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.91,0:13:19.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was tentatively identified as Hideaki Oda, the manager of a tourism company.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.61,0:13:23.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A private detective who knew him is going up to make a positive ID.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.83,0:13:26.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A detective? Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.05,0:13:29.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Detective Yokomizo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.38,0:13:33.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0} himself! It's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.16,0:13:34.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.91,0:13:36.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just happened to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.84,0:13:40.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To get straight to the point, what do you think of this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.85,0:13:43.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From the evidence, it looks like a suicide, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.11,0:13:49.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the circunstances are strange, but it's definitely not murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.02,0:13:51.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What makes you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.57,0:13:54.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First, Oda-{\i1}san{\i0} must have weighed about 100 kg.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.74,0:13:57.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He is very heavy,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.02,0:13:59.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so a normal person wouldn't be able to carry him all the way up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.79,0:14:02.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And even if the killer managed to carry him up,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.45,0:14:07.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the stairwell is too narrow for more than one adult to pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.87,0:14:11.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be possible to drag him up, but in that case, his clothes would get torn,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.44,0:14:13.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the body would get bruised.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.56,0:14:16.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I didn't notice any of those just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.84,0:14:20.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You deduced quite a lot already!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.31,0:14:22.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would he have chosen this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.23,0:14:26.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A little bit more, a little bit more!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.52,0:14:28.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.67,0:14:38.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}This mark is fresh. How did it get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.47,0:14:44.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}The rope's new, but it's frayed in some spots...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.18,0:14:44.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.81,0:14:45.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Pull!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.25,0:14:49.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How are we getting him down? He doesn't reach the railing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.31,0:14:52.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.36,0:14:54.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If his feet can't reach the railing, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.42,0:14:58.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you doing here, kid? Get down!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.52,0:15:04.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking for the toilet, and got lost... Looks like it's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.92,0:15:07.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How strange. Where could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.78,0:15:10.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.30,0:15:11.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Beats me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.19,0:15:13.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the crime lab,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.95,0:15:17.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there wasn't much dust inside the pagoda,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.25,0:15:19.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so they couldn't find the victim's footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.71,0:15:25.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We had the town doctor do an autopsy, and he didn't find any external injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.81,0:15:28.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The cause of death was thus determined to be suffocation due to pressure on the neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.62,0:15:33.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, he died from being hung here...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.52,0:15:38.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The estimated time of death is between 3 and 4 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.57,0:15:41.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Oda was using a suite in his hotel as an office and home,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.02,0:15:47.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but the receptionist says he saw Mr. Oda exit the building at about 2:30 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.35,0:15:53.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the time, I think it's safe to assume he came straight here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.92,0:15:54.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Any will?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.67,0:15:56.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't found any yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.33,0:15:57.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,President!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.50,0:16:04.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,President, why did you kill yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.33,0:16:07.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You should have waited a little more. Just a little more...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.77,0:16:09.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.27,0:16:14.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Hotel Oda's general manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.33,0:16:16.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Kajimura.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.42,0:16:19.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you weren't here last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.77,0:16:21.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. I had a sudden business trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.49,0:16:26.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know any reason why he'd commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.93,0:16:31.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, the purpose of my business trip was to raise funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.01,0:16:38.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If I failed, the checks the company wrote this month would bounce.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.99,0:16:43.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't the only one—the president was worried about it, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.35,0:16:47.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he was carrying a lot of money last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.74,0:16:52.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The president was a very proud man, so he would never show weakness to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.71,0:16:56.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He kept putting on a bold front.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.85,0:17:02.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But yesterday, when the temple people threatened to take him to court,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.62,0:17:04.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he looked extremely worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.57,0:17:05.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.88,0:17:09.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't have his wallet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.89,0:17:11.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The wallet?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.22,0:17:14.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't find any in his possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.72,0:17:16.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it look weird to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.34,0:17:18.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If Oda-{\i1}san{\i0} didn't change his clothes after he had dinner with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.77,0:17:21.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,why did the wallet that he carried last night disappear?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.40,0:17:26.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot!{baaro} Who would have thought of going out with so much money when committing suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.97,0:17:31.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop butting your nose around the scene. I keep having to tell you this!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.52,0:17:34.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But his tie pin's gone, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.46,0:17:41.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay? You can't interfere with the police work...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.88,0:17:45.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}, what did he mean about the pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.49,0:17:47.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oda-{\i1}san{\i0} had one on last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.37,0:17:51.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a five-carat diamond tie pin that really stood out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.67,0:17:55.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it would appear that it's gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.21,0:17:59.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means he could've been robbed!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.52,0:18:01.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, even if he was robbed,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.91,0:18:06.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he was on his way to commit suicide, so he'd probably give up his possessions easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.55,0:18:11.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So this doesn't disprove the suicide theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.49,0:18:15.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If he'd been strangled,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.26,0:18:19.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he'd have struggled trying to free himself, and scratch his own throat with his fingernails.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.22,0:18:22.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there are no traces of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.40,0:18:26.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And even if this was a murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.11,0:18:31.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,how would the killer be able to hang the victim from the pagoda?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.73,0:18:36.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aside from suicide, it's physically impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.13,0:18:41.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if there {\i1}was{\i0} a killer here,\Nthen it'd be that curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.67,0:18:42.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It {\i1}is{\i0} the curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.63,0:18:47.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Heaven punished the unbeliever!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.48,0:18:52.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Detective Yokomizo of the Shizuoka Prefectural Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.13,0:18:53.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,May I ask who you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.13,0:18:56.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.58,0:18:59.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm this temple's head priest, Tankai.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.80,0:19:02.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I am his son, Shunkai.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.23,0:19:04.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Okabe, a temple employee.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.51,0:19:11.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you all tell me where you were and what you were doing yesterday between 3 and 4 AM?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:13.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.17,0:19:14.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't this a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.93,0:19:17.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't come to any conclusion yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.53,0:19:21.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And since some of Oda-{\i1}san{\i0}'s valuables are missing...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.90,0:19:23.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.75,0:19:27.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you accusing us, servants of Buddha, of being vulgar thieves?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.91,0:19:32.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, of course not, but we need your alibis for our records...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.24,0:19:38.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd probably like it if I said I was meeting with that no-good liar,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.61,0:19:41.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I was in the main hall chanting at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.19,0:19:46.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chanting? You were chanting at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.77,0:19:50.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a premonition that the curse would come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.41,0:19:53.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The... curse?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.67,0:19:56.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Shunkai-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.72,0:20:00.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was asleep—I got up at 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.77,0:20:04.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Okabe came to tell me that Oda was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.17,0:20:09.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so shocked that I called Mouri-{\i1}sensei{\i0} right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.71,0:20:15.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Why did you call Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0} first instead of the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.07,0:20:18.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This man is Oda's spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.12,0:20:20.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who introduced me to Oda in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.75,0:20:27.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tankai-{\i1}sama{\i0}, Oda told me he wanted to help the temple by increasing tourists!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.20,0:20:29.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He... He lied to me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.72,0:20:31.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You too?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.40,0:20:35.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like he fooled the head priest here and got the temple's deed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.87,0:20:39.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So three people hated Oda-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.02,0:20:43.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So what if we did?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.75,0:20:49.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That private detective just said you can't disprove the suicide theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.23,0:20:53.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And if it's a suicide, then there's no killer, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.03,0:20:56.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't concluded it as a suicide yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.99,0:21:00.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then make a decision already, and get off my property!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.77,0:21:04.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stand having these sacred grounds trampled by those who are impure!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.61,0:21:10.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Oda-{\i1}san{\i0}'s wallet and tie pin are indeed missing,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.02,0:21:13.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}but everything seems to be pointing to a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.64,0:21:18.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}But something doesn't fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.68,0:21:24.07,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}His elbow's dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.27,0:21:30.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Grass? Did he fall and hit his elbow?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.82,0:21:38.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}There's dirt on his heels!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.28,0:21:40.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Why would there be dirt there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.12,0:21:43.12,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.01,0:21:47.46,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}If you look closer, you can see the rope is charred!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.27,0:21:49.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.59,0:21:58.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Found it! There's his tie pin!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.78,0:22:00.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Now I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.11,0:22:02.12,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}This is the true crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.39,0:22:11.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}If my deduction is right, then Oda-{\i1}san{\i0} didn't kill himself, he was murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.22,0:22:17.99,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}And the one who did it was him, the one who said {\i1}that{\i0} back then!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.25,0:24:09.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(136,104)\fnSegoe\fscx105\fs28\fsp1\shad0\bord0\alpha&H1F&}NEXT EPISODE
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.98,0:23:47.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.32,0:23:52.36,Dialogue,,0010,0010,0000,,If he stood on the railing and his neck didn't reach the rope, then he couldn't have committed suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.36,0:23:55.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just say for the sake of argument that it was a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.40,0:24:00.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How would the killer hang him with a rope that was 50 cm too short?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.75,0:24:02.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.91,0:24:05.87,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}This side was tied to the railing...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.87,0:24:09.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}But why did the killer use an artillery loop?
